</table>
<p><b>Thomas Day</b> (22 June 1748 – 28 September 1789) was a British author and <a href="/wiki/Abolitionist" class="mw-redirect" title="Abolitionist">abolitionist</a>. He was well known for the children's book <i><a href="/wiki/The_History_of_Sandford_and_Merton" title="The History of Sandford and Merton">The History of Sandford and Merton</a></i> (1783–1789) which emphasized Rousseauvian educational ideals.</p>
<p></p>
