<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Bibliography">Bibliography</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Thomas_Day&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Bibliography">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="refbegin columns references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em;">
<ul>
<li>Blackman, John. <i>A Memoir of the Life and Writings of Thomas Day, author of “Sandford and Merton.”</i> London: <a href="/wiki/John_Bedford_Leno" title="John Bedford Leno">John Bedford Leno</a>, 1862.</li>
<li>Chandler, Anne. "Defying ‘Development’: Thomas Day's Queer Curriculum in <i>Sandford and Merton</i>." <i>Novel Gazing: Queer Readings in Fiction</i>. Ed. <a href="/wiki/Eve_Kosofsky_Sedgwick" title="Eve Kosofsky Sedgwick">Eve Kosofsky Sedgwick</a>. Durham: Duke University Press, 1997.</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFFraser.27s1832" class="citation journal"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.ca/books?id=pnA-AQAAMAAJ">"Miss Edgeworlh's Tales and Novels"</a>. <i>Fraser's Magazine</i>. <b>6</b> (November): 541–558. 1832<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">18 March</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThomas+Day&amp;rft.atitle=Miss+Edgeworlh%27s+Tales+and+Novels&amp;rft.date=1832&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.ca%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DpnA-AQAAMAAJ&amp;rft.issue=November&amp;rft.jtitle=Fraser%27s+Magazine&amp;rft.pages=541-558&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=6" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>Gignilliat, George Warren, Jr. <i>The Author of Sandford and Merton: A Life of Thomas Day, Esq</i>. New York: Columbia University Press, 1932.</li>
<li><cite class="citation book"><a href="/wiki/James_Keir" title="James Keir">Keir, James</a> (1791). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=s900AAAAMAAJ&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;dq=james+keir"><i>An Account of the Life and Writings of Thomas Day, Esq.</i></a> London: John Stockdale.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThomas+Day&amp;rft.au=Keir%2C+James&amp;rft.btitle=An+Account+of+the+Life+and+Writings+of+Thomas+Day%2C+Esq.&amp;rft.date=1791&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Ds900AAAAMAAJ%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%26dq%3Djames%2Bkeir&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=John+Stockdale&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFMoore2013" class="citation book"><a href="/wiki/Wendy_Moore" title="Wendy Moore">Moore, Wendy</a> (2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.ca/books?id=KEc36eNHl7AC"><i>How to create the perfect wife Britain's most ineligible bachelor and his enlightened quest to train the ideal mate</i></a>. New York: Basic Books. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780465065738" title="Special:BookSources/9780465065738">9780465065738</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThomas+Day&amp;rft.aufirst=Wendy&amp;rft.aulast=Moore&amp;rft.btitle=How+to+create+the+perfect+wife+Britain%27s+most+ineligible+bachelor+and+his+enlightened+quest+to+train+the+ideal+mate&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.ca%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DKEc36eNHl7AC&amp;rft.isbn=9780465065738&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Basic+Books&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
